Food.create(name: 'Baked Halibut with Chimichurri', description: 'Though you might normally associate chimichurri with grilled steaks, lamb chops and other robust cuts of meat, this garlicky South American herb sauce pairs wonderfully with mild halibut and other lean white fish. Rubbed over the fillets before baking, the flavor of the chimichurri stays fresh and bright, infusing the delicate fish with a pop of green color and taste that says SPRING! It’s another simple yet impressive fish recipe to add to your repertoire.', recipe_url: 'https://www.thekitchn.com/recipe-baked-chimichurri-halibut-recipes-from-the-kitchn-188598', image_url: 'https://cdn.apartmenttherapy.info/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:eco,c_fit,w_1460/https%3A%2F%2Fstorage.googleapis.com%2Fgen-atmedia%2F3%2F2013%2F04%2F776b41009266678a4ce808fa766dd2aa11224e9f.jpeg', mood_id: 1)
Food.create(name: 'Vietnamese Beef Noodle Pho', description: 'Vietnamese beef noodle pho is an easy soup to fall in love with. Those chewy noodles, that savory broth, the tender slices of beef — all those crunchy, spicy, herby garnishes we get to toss on top. On a cold evening, after a rough day at work, when we’re sick, on a lazy weekend afternoon — a bowl of piping hot pho is pretty much always a good idea.', recipe_url: 'https://www.thekitchn.com/how-to-make-quick-vietnamese-beef-pho-cooking-lessons-from-the-kitchn-215118', image_url: 'https://cdn.apartmenttherapy.info/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:eco,c_fit,w_1460/https%3A%2F%2Fstorage.googleapis.com%2Fgen-atmedia%2F3%2F2015%2F01%2Feb84435688acfbb9c988f165b754bb3a989df6b5.jpeg', mood_id: 2)
Food.create(name: 'Easy Slow Cooker Beef Stroganoff', description: 'Family-friendly classics don’t have to start with a can of condensed soup. This easy beef stroganoff is just as comforting as the one you grew up with, but is made with fresh mushrooms and a simple gravy that comes together as the ingredients braise in the slow cooker. It requires minimal upfront prep (no stovetop browning!), meaning you can toss in all the ingredients in the morning and then return to a warm dinner in the evening.', recipe_url: 'https://www.thekitchn.com/slow-cooker-beef-stroganoff-265025', image_url: 'https://cdn.apartmenttherapy.info/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:eco,c_fit,w_1460/https%3A%2F%2Fstorage.googleapis.com%2Fgen-atmedia%2F3%2F2019%2F01%2Fe1ea1acf00ff5d98f8deed1b2c8223af59a5c09c.jpeg', mood_id: 3)
Food.create(name: 'Bubble and Squeak', description: 'Bubble and squeak, with its cutesy name, is a classic British day-after-holiday dish. It is incredibly versatile, as you can throw in any leftover vegetables or mashed potatoes into this comforting recipe — perfect for a relaxing meal after a hectic Thanksgiving.', recipe_url: 'https://www.thekitchn.com/recipe-bubble-and-squeak-recipes-from-the-kitchn-213148', image_url: 'https://cdn.apartmenttherapy.info/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:eco,c_fit,w_1460/https%3A%2F%2Fstorage.googleapis.com%2Fgen-atmedia%2F3%2F2014%2F11%2Fd2232838000d100ee9863248086dfb367e4a551e.jpeg', mood_id: 4)
Food.create(name: 'Chicken & Dumplings', description: 'On a busy weekend day when you have a lot of things to take care of around the house but not much time to devote to dinner, pull this slow cooker chicken and dumpling recipe out of your back pocket. This comforting dish — with tender chicken swimming in a creamy sauce filled with herbs and vegetables that’s topped with tender dumplings — requires very little attention on your part, but you’re rewarded with a dinner that tastes like you’ve been standing at the stove all day.', recipe_url: 'https://www.thekitchn.com/recipe-slow-cooker-chicken-amp-dumplings-253309', image_url: 'https://cdn.apartmenttherapy.info/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:eco,c_fit,w_1460/https%3A%2F%2Fstorage.googleapis.com%2Fgen-atmedia%2F3%2F2018%2F01%2Ffef187547dd879130efed81d02568b2e5efaacb3.jpeg', mood_id: 5)
Food.create(name: 'Kale Salad with Apricots, Avocado & Parmesan', description: 'I’ve been eating this salad of raw kale tossed in a red wine vinaigrette almost every day for the past month. I love the way the chewy bits of dried apricots and the creamy avocado contrast with the heartiness of the kale. A handful of almonds, a spoonful of beans, and a few flakes of salty parmesan turn this salad into a very satisfying meal. Yes, I thought it high time this recipe was shared.', recipe_url: 'https://www.thekitchn.com/lunch-for-one-kale-salad-with-148328', image_url: 'https://www.thekitchn.com/lunch-for-one-kale-salad-with-148328', mood_id: 6)
Food.create(name: 'Green Eggs and Ham', description: 'Leave it to Dr. Seuss to inspire a breakfast as whimsical and cheery as green eggs and ham. It’s probably safe to say since the book Green Eggs and Ham was published in 1960, parents have been trying to find a way to create the titular dish for eager children.', recipe_url: 'https://www.thekitchn.com/how-to-make-green-eggs-and-ham-242334', image_url: 'https://cdn.apartmenttherapy.info/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:eco,c_fit,w_1460/https%3A%2F%2Fstorage.googleapis.com%2Fgen-atmedia%2F3%2F2017%2F03%2F736d92e150f7619f79df76992250b842a480331b.jpeg', mood_id: 7)
Food.create(name: 'Scallops', description: 'Scallops are a little luxury in my household. A weekend date night means plates of pasta and scallops with wedges of lemon and glasses of white wine on the side. Scallops are sustainable, delicious, and so easy! Here’s how to make quick-cooking scallops on the stovetop in just about five minutes.', recipe_url: 'https://www.thekitchn.com/how-to-cook-scallops-on-the-stovetop-cooking-lessons-from-the-kitchn-203516', image_url: 'https://cdn.apartmenttherapy.info/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:eco,c_fit,w_1460/https%3A%2F%2Fstorage.googleapis.com%2Fgen-atmedia%2F3%2F2014%2F05%2F48b592862e7c9969e57ddce40caa4fac8b10955b.jpeg', mood_id: 8)
Food.create(name: 'Saag Paneer Pizza', description: 'Saag paneer is a spiced, creamy spinach stew finished with soft pieces of mild paneer cheese. The main topping for this pizza version is basically a sauté of frozen spinach with onion, garlic, ginger, and garam masala. It gets its rich flavor and texture from the addition of cream at the end, which works to hold everything together.', recipe_url: 'https://www.thekitchn.com/recipe-saag-paneer-pizza-230117', image_url: 'https://cdn.apartmenttherapy.info/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:eco,c_fit,w_1460/https%3A%2F%2Fstorage.googleapis.com%2Fgen-atmedia%2F3%2F2016%2F06%2F02fb9e5e7cf763506cb18d4185c22f5f37651fe3.jpeg', mood_id: 9)
Food.create(name: 'Hot as a Torch! Baked Jalapeño Poppers', description: 'We go right for Cabot cheese, which is owned by a co-operative of 1,100 farm families throughout New England and New York. The Cabot farmers raise happy cows because happy cows produce rich, buttery milk that becomes cheese that wins awards year after year.', recipe_url: 'https://www.thekitchn.com/3-cheesy-recipes-for-your-game-day-bash-240961', image_url: 'https://cdn.apartmenttherapy.info/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:eco,c_fit,w_1460/https%3A%2F%2Fstorage.googleapis.com%2Fgen-atmedia%2F3%2F2017%2F01%2Fd6f82b1a2feafafc0d7945e62777f4c3eeae4766.jpeg', mood_id: 10)
Food.create(name: 'Lyonnaise Salad', description: 'We have a lot to thank France for when it comes to mealtime, but perhaps one of my favorites is Lyonnaise Salad, or Salade Lyonniase: it’s a perfect combination of frisée, a curly bitter salad green, tossed in a warm vinaigrette and topped with a poached egg and crispy thick-slab bacon pieces. It’s one of those timeless dishes that hits the spot every time and can transport you to the banks of the Seine even if you’re stuck in your sweltering American apartment.', recipe_url: 'https://www.thekitchn.com/recipe-lyonnaise-salad-recipes-from-the-kitchn-4418', image_url: 'https://cdn.apartmenttherapy.info/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:eco,c_fit,w_1460/https%3A%2F%2Fstorage.googleapis.com%2Fgen-atmedia%2F3%2F2014%2F07%2F0659fbc5cb007e0009ab5c7d6e430aa6c1527eb6.jpeg', mood_id: 11)
Food.create(name: 'Honey-Sesame Tofu and Green Beans', description: 'Perhaps the most time-intensive element of this recipe is waiting for the tofu to dry out. That’s when you do the rest of the prep — making the sauce and cutting the veggies — so by the time you pop everything into the oven to cook, the 10 minutes or so it takes goes by in a flash. Would you expect anything less from a recipe from Damn Delicious?', recipe_url: 'https://www.thekitchn.com/recipe-sheet-pan-sesame-tofu-and-green-beans-235980', image_url: 'https://cdn.apartmenttherapy.info/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:eco,c_fit,w_1460/https%3A%2F%2Fstorage.googleapis.com%2Fgen-atmedia%2F3%2F2016%2F09%2Fc0f5fc5b67c1369bcb12c6645532a084a3622289.jpeg', mood_id: 12)
Food.create(name: 'Polenta with Spring Vegetable Ragout', description: 'We’re sharing the details of an Italian Polenta Supper featuring lots of toppings, like hearty braised beef, on a bed of creamy cornmeal polenta. For a lighter, vegan-friendly accompaniment to polenta, let me suggest this spring vegetable ragout. Like the braised beef, it’s rustic and uncomplicated yet completely dinner-party worthy. Make it now if you’re already basking in the glow of peas and asparagus, or save this recipe so you can celebrate the moment spring arrives.', recipe_url: 'https://www.thekitchn.com/recipe-polenta-with-spring-vegetable-ragout-recipes-from-the-kitchn-186581', image_url: 'https://cdn.apartmenttherapy.info/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:eco,c_fit,w_1460/https%3A%2F%2Fstorage.googleapis.com%2Fgen-atmedia%2F3%2F2013%2F03%2Fd9ed19fd317cd28c37e915fb0c948bcd4296b402.jpeg', mood_id: 13)
Food.create(name: 'Garlic Butter Steak and Potatoes', description: 'When you’re hankering for a classic steak and potatoes dinner, this one-skillet dish fits the bill perfectly. What makes it extra special is the garlicky lemon-parsley butter that’s basted over the steak as it’s seared. You end up with all the flavors of a steakhouse, except from the comfort of your own home.', recipe_url: 'https://www.thekitchn.com/garlic-steak-and-potatoes-258348', image_url: 'https://cdn.apartmenttherapy.info/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:eco,c_fit,w_1460/https%3A%2F%2Fstorage.googleapis.com%2Fgen-atmedia%2F3%2F2018%2F07%2F85cec2ec415704ce1e9bbe3cd9cff9a0aef40fe2.jpeg', mood_id: 14)
Food.create(name: 'Cold Peanut Sesame Noodles with Chicken', description: 'Cold may be a strong word to use for this dish — it’s really more room temperature if you serve it right away, but it tastes great leftover, straight out of the fridge, so change the name as you wish. Chilly Peanut Sesame Noodles just didn’t sound quite right to me.', recipe_url: 'https://www.thekitchn.com/recipe-cold-peanut-sesame-noodles-with-chicken-53032', image_url: 'https://cdn.apartmenttherapy.info/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:eco,c_fit,w_1460/https%3A%2F%2Fstorage.googleapis.com%2Fgen-atmedia%2F3%2F2015%2F08%2F3507c1c91499eca784208cd7d684db89c99b76a3.jpeg', mood_id: 15)
Food.create(name: 'French Onion Soup Grilled Cheese', description: 'My ultimate “bowl” of onion soup is one part soup, one part toasted bread, and one part melty cheese. Not exactly the ratio the French stand behind, but it works for me. Why not make a “quickie” French onion soup grilled cheese?', recipe_url: 'https://www.thekitchn.com/recipe-french-onion-soup-grilled-cheese-recipes-from-the-kitchn-182119', image_url: 'https://cdn.apartmenttherapy.info/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:eco,c_fit,w_1460/https%3A%2F%2Fstorage.googleapis.com%2Fgen-atmedia%2F3%2F2013%2F01%2Fe336298cf1055bead49101085cd3dc6b3933d979.jpeg', mood_id: 16)

Drink.create(name: 'Pink Lemonade Margarita', description: "Meet margarita's sassy sister.", drink_url: 'https://www.delish.com/cooking/recipe-ideas/recipes/a53281/pink-senoritas-recipe/', image_url: 'https://s3.amazonaws.com/reviews-photos-drinkedin.drinkedin.net/original/7d/07/b3/pink-lemonade-margarita-84-1363611535.jpg', mood_id: 1)
Drink.create(name: 'Green Tea', description: 'Green tea does have more health benefits than black tea which can be attributed to its lack of processing. Green tea is higher in protective polyphenols. The major polyphenols in green tea are flavonoids, the most active of which are catechins and epigallocatechin gallate (EGCG) which function as powerful antioxidants. Antioxidants are known to protect the body against disease and are an important part of a healthy diet. Antioxidants can be found in a range of fruits, vegetables and other unprocessed foods. As part of a balanced diet, green tea can be a good source of antioxidants.', drink_url: '', image_url: 'https://images-prod.healthline.com/hlcmsresource/images/AN_images/AN79-Green_tea_on_wood-732x549-Thumb_0.jpg', mood_id: 2)
Drink.create(name: 'Scotch', description: "True Scotch Whisky reflects the land of it's birthplace, and the people who created it, in many ways. It is traditionally made from barley and pure, clear water - both of which are in plentiful supply in Scotland. It also needs a cool, damp or moist environment in order to mature properly, again there's plenty of cool weather and moisture in Scotland! Scotland is a country which historically has proven it's strength and courage and fought fiercely for it's independence. So perhaps it's no surprise that Scotch Whisky is a drink which could be described as bold, strong and fiery... although it can also be smooth, almost sweet, a drink of depth and contrasts - just like Scotland itself!", drink_url: '', image_url: 'http://eatupnewyork.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/ThinkstockPhotos-101435749.jpg', mood_id: 3)
Drink.create(name: 'Butterbeer', description: 'Straight out of Harry Potter, Butterbeer was a popular wizarding beverage described as tasting "a little bit like less-sickly butterscotch". It was served at numerous locations in the wizarding world and had a very slight alcoholic content. Students of Hogwarts School of Witchcraft and Wizardry would often buy it when visiting Hogsmeade.', drink_url: 'https://harrypotter.fandom.com/wiki/Butterbeer', image_url: 'https://www.favfamilyrecipes.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/Harry-Potter-Butterbeer.jpg', mood_id: 4)
Drink.create(name: 'London Fog', description: "London Fog Drink It's Earl Grey tea, milk, vanilla extract, and sugar. Basically, a London Fog is an Earl Grey tea latte dressed up with vanilla and sugar. It's perfect pick-me-up on a dreary day.", drink_url: 'http://blog.davidstea.com/en/how-to-make-a-london-fog-tea-latte/', image_url: 'http://blog.davidstea.com/en/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/Fall2017_NonCampaign_34702_LondonFog_Pinterest-1-768x1151.jpg', mood_id: 5)
Drink.create(name: 'Yerba Mate', description: 'Yerba mate is an herbal tea made from the leaves and twigs of the Ilex paraguariensis plant. The leaves are typically dried over a fire, then steeped in hot water to make the tea. Yerba mate is traditionally consumed from a container called a gourd and sipped with a metal straw that has a filter at its lower end to strain out the leaf fragments. Sharing it from this traditional gourd is said to be a sign of friendship and bonding.', drink_url: '', image_url: 'https://cdn-statics.thebubble.com/wp-content/uploads/mate-y-madera.jpg', mood_id: 6)
Drink.create(name: 'Cotton Candy Champagne', description: "Start with a fluff of cotton candy in your glass. It's a whimsical touch that will bring out your childlike side for two reasons: (1) Cotton candy just looks so freaking adorable, and (2) when you pour Champagne over cotton candy, it melts into the liquid, making for a really cool party trick and a fun Champagne cocktail in one. As an alternative, place a smaller pouf of cotton candy on top of a full glass for a cloud-like effect.", drink_url: '', image_url: 'https://hips.hearstapps.com/cos.h-cdn.co/assets/15/52/768x993/gallery-1450719184-champagne-cotton-candy.jpg?resize=768:*', mood_id: 7)
Drink.create(name: '2013 Dievole Chianti Classico', description: 'This is the bottle for those who like a wine that’s intense but not overpowering. It offers sensual violet aromas and a parade of aphrodisiac notes on the tongue: tobacco, leather and lingering spice. Despite the intensity, its smooth tannins and good acidity make it surprisingly easy drinking. (And who doesn’t look sexy drinking Italian wine?)', drink_url: '', image_url: 'https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0070/5162/products/Villa_Cappelli_Italian_food_red_wine.jpg?v=1456935764', mood_id: 8)
Drink.create(name: '', description: "Pulque, traditional to central Mexico, is a milk-colored, somewhat viscous liquid that produces a light foam. It is made by fermenting the sap of certain types of maguey (agave) plants. In contrast, mezcal is made from the cooked heart of certain agave plants, and tequila, a variety of mezcal, is made all or mostly from the blue agave. About six varieties of maguey are best used for the production of pulque. The name pulque is derived from Nahuatl. The original name of the drink was iztāc octli [ˈistaːk ˈokt͡ɬi] (white pulque), the term pulque was probably mistakenly derived by the Spanish from the octli poliuhqui [ˈokt͡ɬi poˈliwki], which meant 'spoiled pulque'", drink_url: 'https://www.seriouseats.com/2019/02/introduction-to-pulque.html', image_url: 'https://cdn.theculturetrip.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/mctp0020-pulqueria-mexico-city-mexico-lauckner-75-featured.jpg', mood_id: 9)
Drink.create(name: 'Bloody Mary', description: 'A Bloody Mary is a cocktail containing vodka, tomato juice, and combinations of other spices and flavorings including Worcestershire sauce, hot sauces, garlic, herbs, horseradish, celery, olives, salt, black pepper, lemon juice, lime juice and/or celery salt. In the United States, it is usually consumed in the morning or early afternoon, and is popular as a hangover cure. The Bloody Mary was invented in the 1920s or 1930s; there are various theories as to the origin of the drink, as well as the origin of its name. It has many variants, most notably the Red Snapper, the Virgin Mary, the Caesar, and the Michelada.', drink_url: 'https://www.liquor.com/slideshows/best-bloody-mary-recipes/#gs.v4qdbx', image_url: 'https://www.tabasco.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/Tabasco-Bloody-Mary-Show-Me-the-Yummy-5@2x.jpg', mood_id: 10)
Drink.create(name: 'Water', description: 'While staying hydrated may not get rid of anxiety entirely, it can help reduce its intensity. Additionally, according to the Calm Clinic. Water also appears to have natural calming properties. Drinking water can be soothing, and often your body will benefit from the added hydration during times of intense stress.', drink_url: '', image_url: 'https://article.images.consumerreports.org/f_auto/prod/content/dam/CRO%20Images%202019/Health/06June/CR-Health-Inlinehero-stay-hydrated-0619', mood_id: 11)
Drink.create(name: 'Apple Cider or Hard Cider', description: 'Cider is an alcoholic beverage made from the fermented juice of apples', drink_url: '', image_url: 'https://www.countyengraving.co.uk/ekmps/shops/countyengraving/images/aspall-cider-pint-glass-personalised-27652-p.jpg', mood_id: 12)
Drink.create(name: 'Honey Cinnamon Latte', description: "This Honey Cinnamon Latte is my go-to when I need a quick pick-me-up or something comforting.  And what is more comforting and relaxing than the smell of cinnamon.", drink_url: 'https://queenbeeskitchen.com/honey-cinnamon-latte/', image_url: 'https://i0.wp.com/queenbeeskitchen.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/honey-cin-latte_2016_407b.jpg?w=680&ssl=1', mood_id: 13)
Drink.create(name: 'Jäger Bomb', description: "Jägermeister is a strong liqueur with a slight anise taste. The 'depressant' effects of the alcohol are offset by the energy drink Red Bull that it is dropped into, which can definitely help keep the party going. And yet, this is not a shot for lightweights or the faint of heart.", drink_url: '', image_url: 'https://www.comfy-homes.co.uk/media/catalog/product/cache/1/small_image/800x800/85e4522595efc69f496374d01ef2bf13/0/0/00130.jpg', mood_id: 14)
Drink.create(name: 'A Shot in the Dark', description: "Have you ever been in an elevator and wondered why you can't go to the top floor? Have you ever wondered why you have to sit on the left or right and not in the middle when driving your car? Have you ever wondered why you have to pick just one friend to be stuck on a deserted island with? If you have, then this is the drink for you. Forget wondering if you should have a drip coffee or an espresso, we have combined the best of both worlds in one drink. A Shot In The Dark is a perfectly extracted dose of our espresso poured atop a steamy cup of our flavourful medium or dark roasted fresh brewed drip coffee. Now your only choice is between medium or dark roast...or both!", drink_url: '', image_url: 'https://keto2fast.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/coffee-autophagy.jpg', mood_id: 15)
Drink.create(name: 'Vanilla Steamer', description: "A soul-warming non-caffeinated drink for a winter's day or nightcap", drink_url: '', image_url: 'https://www.dessertfortwo.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/copycat-starbucks-vanilla-steamer-fb.jpg', mood_id: 15)

Dessert.create(name: 'Pavlova with Blueberry Jam', description: "If you’ve never tried Pavlova before you might be curious what it tastes like. It’s a meringue dessert, so it’s crunchy on the outside and soft on the inside. It reminds me of what I’d imagine a baked marshmallow to taste like. And Pavlova is usually served with whipped cream and berries. I decided to skip the whipped cream (but feel free to add it in if you want) and make a quick blueberry jam to top these.", recipe_url: 'https://abeautifulmess.com/2013/08/pavlova-with-blueberry-jam.html', image_url: 'https://images.abeautifulmess.com/uploads/typekit/.a/6a00d8358081ff69e20192ac6bb0be970d-800wi', mood_id: 1)
Dessert.create(name: 'Crème Brûlée', description: "Five simple ingredients – cream, vanilla, salt, eggs and sugar – make for an exquisitely rich and elegant dessert.", recipe_url: 'https://cooking.nytimes.com/recipes/9039-vanilla-creme-brulee', image_url: 'https://bakingamoment.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/IMG_5462-creme-brulee.jpg', mood_id: 2)
Dessert.create(name: 'Salted Dark Chocolate Stout Cake', description: "This dark chocolate stout cake is absolutely divine! It's ridiculously rich. Pumpkin stout batter is baked into fluffy laters and covered in a super fudgy chocolate ganache. Perfect for chocolate lovers!", recipe_url: 'https://www.howsweeteats.com/2018/10/dark-chocolate-stout-cake/', image_url: 'https://www.howsweeteats.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/salted-chocolate-cake-I-howsweeteats.com-6.jpg', mood_id: 3)
Dessert.create(name: 'Worms in Dirt', description: "When I was a kid, worms in dirt were the ultimate Halloween party dessert (what 8-year old doesn’t love chocolate pudding and Oreos?), and I’m not at all embarrassed to admit that not much has changed since then. It’s been quite a while since I could say a dessert made me flat out giddy but I must say, this one definitely did. The nostalgia alone was enough to get me going — and it doesn’t hurt that the assembly is an edible art project on its own — but what I truly love about these Grown-Up Worms in Dirt is that they’re practically oozing with Halloween spirit, while packing most of my favorite things into one fun little container. This version features an intensely rich bourbon-spiked dark chocolate pudding, layered with seasonal-favorite pumpkin spice pudding and topped the traditional embellishments: crushed Oreos, two types gummy worms and a few googly eyes for good measure. In a moment of ambition I chose to make my pudding from scratch, but you can certainly go the semi-homemade route and use instant pudding mix instead (see shortcut notes in the recipe), and don’t be afraid to tweak the flavors to fit your preference or theme — a blood-red velvet pudding would be scarily good here! Enjoy!", recipe_url: 'http://www.jacquelynclark.com/2015/10/29/halloween-dessert-worms-in-dirt/', image_url: 'http://www.jacquelynclark.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/10/Grown-Up-Worms-in-Dirt-39.jpg', mood_id: 4)
Dessert.create(name: 'Earl Grey Tea Ice Cream', description: "Not surprisingly—black tea, combined with bergamot oil, cuts through the summer heat about as well as anything. We use a high-quality loose tea from our favorite tea brand, Rishi, which uses pure Italian bergamot citrus oil (and not bergamot flavoring), to make the most intensely fragrant Earl Grey tea ice cream.", recipe_url: 'https://www.epicurious.com/recipes/food/views/earl-grey-tea-ice-cream-56389790', image_url: 'https://i.pinimg.com/originals/46/6a/d0/466ad034fc5a9eabe4446ad76cdbb4b1.jpg', mood_id: 5)
Dessert.create(name: 'Italian Sweet Easter Egg Bread', description: "This Italian Easter bread has a strong Sicilian accent and carries the taste of spring all baked into joy-filled, adorable little wreaths. The bread is strongly spiced and rich with anise as a little reminder of winter. Down to the colorful sprinkles, this bread celebrates the breaking of the Lenten fast.", recipe_url: 'https://www.thekitchn.com/italian-easter-bread-recipe-255480', image_url: 'https://cdn.apartmenttherapy.info/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:eco,c_fit,w_1460/https%3A%2F%2Fstorage.googleapis.com%2Fgen-atmedia%2F3%2F2019%2F04%2F6fcdcb2221a2bdb6a2c0a3112758564475894647.jpeg', mood_id: 6)
Dessert.create(name: 'Mini Pineapple Upside Down Cake ', description: "These Mini Pineapple Upside-Down Cakes are simple, sweet, and sure to put a smile on everyone's face!", recipe_url: 'https://bakerbynature.com/mini-pineapple-upside-down-cakes/', image_url: 'https://bakerbynature.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/pineapple-upside-down-cakes-26-of-59.jpg', mood_id: 7)
Dessert.create(name: 'Chocolate Covered Strawberry Cheesecakes', description: "Speaking of rich, silky treats, these mini cheesecakes are perfect for Valentine’s Day. Feel free to serve them as-is, or get creative with holiday-inspired (think pink hearts and bright colors) cupcake liners.", recipe_url: 'https://www.awayfromthebox.com/chocolate-covered-strawberry-cheesecakes/', image_url: 'https://images.britcdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/Cheesecakes-1-C-645x968.jpg?w=1000&auto=format&q=50', mood_id: 8)
Dessert.create(name: 'Fried Ice Cream', description: "Hot, deep-fried food and cold, frozen ice cream wouldn’t make a winning pair — or so you think. This recipe makes the seemingly impossible come true, and truth be told, it’s not as difficult as it sounds.", recipe_url: 'https://www.thedailymeal.com/fried-ice-cream-recipe', image_url: 'https://thumbor.thedailymeal.com/i1N7GdGtcqh4K4Zor8efxFJa9hU=/870x565/filters:format(webp)/https://www.thedailymeal.com/sites/default/files/slides/9-fried%20ice%20cream-shutterstock_184501088.jpg', mood_id: 9)
Dessert.create(name: 'Pineapple Jalapeño Ice Pops', description: "These Pineapple Jalapeño popsicles are the easiest of all to make and they are really really wonderful.  You have to taste them to believe them.  The  icy cold – sweetness of the pineapple hits your tongue at the same moment the heat of the jalapeño kicks in.", recipe_url: 'https://theviewfromgreatisland.com/pineapple-jalapeno-popsicles/', image_url: 'https://img.buzzfeed.com/buzzfeed-static/static/2015-07/6/10/enhanced/webdr01/enhanced-buzz-23608-1436193364-7.jpg?downsize=800:*&output-format=auto&output-quality=auto', mood_id: 10)
Dessert.create(name: 'Rosemary Lavender Cake ', description: " This is our Vanilla Vanilla Cake recipe filled with a delicious Honey Buttercream and decorated with a little Lavender and Rosemary. All we did to make the honey buttercream was add a little honey to the original vanilla buttercream recipe until it tasted the way we wanted it to. It was super easy and turned out really well!", recipe_url: 'https://www.sprinklesforbreakfast.com/rosemary-lavender-cake.php', image_url: 'https://www.sprinklesforbreakfast.com/images/rosemary-lavender-cake-3.jpeg', mood_id: 11)
Dessert.create(name: 'Macarons', description: "This easy French macaron recipe makes a batch of the most dainty, delicate, and delicious cookies that will float right into your mouth and disappear. I’ve packed all my tips into this post to help you out!", recipe_url: 'https://preppykitchen.com/french-macarons/', image_url: 'https://sugargeekshow.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/01/french-macaroon-recipe.jpg', mood_id: 12)
Dessert.create(name: 'Balsamic Berries with Honey Yogurt', description: "When fresh berries are at their peak mid-summer, I can’t help but eat my weight in them. I sprinkle them onto my morning oatmeal, eat them out of hand midday, and enjoy them as a sweet yet wholesome treat after dinner. This quick recipe embraces the juicy summer fruit and transforms them into a fast and fancy dessert in a matter of minutes. You very well may already have the ingredients in your kitchen right now, which means this could be dessert tonight.", recipe_url: 'https://www.thekitchn.com/balsamic-berries-honey-yogurt-22925320', image_url: 'https://cdn.apartmenttherapy.info/image/upload/f_auto,q_auto:eco,c_fit,w_1460,h_1825/k/Photo/Recipes/2019-07-recipe-balsamic-berries-honey-yogurt/Balsamic-Berries-Honey-Yogurt_061', mood_id: 13)
Dessert.create(name: 'Baked Alaska', description: "Baked Alaska, also known as omelette norvégienne, omelette surprise, or omelette sibérienne depending on the country, is a dessert consisting of ice cream and cake topped with browned meringue. The dish is made of ice cream placed in a pie dish, lined with slices of sponge cake or Christmas pudding, and topped with meringue. The entire dessert is then placed in an extremely hot oven for a brief time, long enough to firm and caramelize the meringue but not long enough to begin melting the ice cream", recipe_url: 'https://smittenkitchen.com/2016/09/baked-alaska-smitten-kitchen-turns-10/', image_url: 'https://www.saveur.com/resizer/N05WxkK-43K-3OpsKd9FBsEyW08=/1008x756/filters:focal(1000x750:1001x751)/arc-anglerfish-arc2-prod-bonnier.s3.amazonaws.com/public/T5OSOMMM77WJ5EYR6M272MHWFU.jpg', mood_id: 14)
Dessert.create(name: 'Lemon Bars', description: "Tart, rich and perfection, all rolled into one! Wow your friends with this simple recipe. Hint: No Substitutions!", recipe_url: 'https://www.allrecipes.com/recipe/10294/the-best-lemon-bars/', image_url: 'https://d213sdapb08052.cloudfront.net/assets/recipes/lemon-bars/_entryTopPhotoMobile/Page-201-web-horizon.jpg?mtime=20160726112614', mood_id: 15)
Dessert.create(name: 'Homemade Chocolate Pudding', description: "Toss out the snack packs and learn how to make homemade chocolate pudding completely from scratch, no box-mix required. This is an easy recipe that has been a hit with my family and is a richly chocolate treat that’s a far cry from the artificially flavored snack packs you can buy at the supermarket.", recipe_url: 'https://sugarspunrun.com/homemade-chocolate-pudding/', image_url: 'https://i2.wp.com/www.sugarspunrun.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/Homemade-Chocolate-Pudding-Recipe-1-of-1-6.jpg', mood_id: 16)
